addRadioMenuItem

                                               java.lang.String itemName,

                                               javax.swing.ButtonGroup group,

                                               boolean selected,

                                               java.lang.String command)
Add a radio button named ITEMNAME to the end of the menu named MENUNAME from the menu bar, placing it in GROUP (only one radio button in a group is selected at a time), initially selecting it iff SELECTED. When the item is selected by the user, causes COMMAND to be used as the action command (see actionPerformed). Returns the new menu item.

                          java.lang.Object... args)

getCommand

getCommand


java.lang.String getCommand(long timeLimit)
Waits for either the next command given to the GUI or TIMELIMIT milliseconds to elapse. If no command arrives within the time limit, returns null. The time limit may be 0, indicating that a command is returned only if the GUI had previously issued it prior to this call.
